Release Notes for Seq66 v. 0.99.21 2025-07-27 "Karl Kleanup"

This release contains fixes and updates for issues #68, #137, #138,
#139, and #140, as well as a number of smaller changes discovered
while fixing these issues. Some minor features added.

- General.
  - A C++17 compiler is now required. Time to move on!
- Main window and grid.
  - Fixed the BBT/HMS button tooltip.
  - The playlist was auto-arming all patterns even when not active.
  - Changing the main time signature changes the time signature in
    all patterns (except for those with a pattern editor open).
- Pattern editor.
  - Pattern-fix dialog.
    - Added randomizing note pitches as per the current musical
      scale for the pattern.
    - Added space above and below the data range and added
      top/bottom lines and value labels. See issue #140.
    - Adding an Insert macros function to the pattern-editor
      Tools menu; see issue #68.
  - Optimized gradient drawing using QLinearGradient members in
    qseqroll instead of auto objects.
  - Made the drawing of pitchbend data show +- pitchbend
    better, i.e. above and below the midline pitchbend, 0.
    Fixes made to pitchbend calculations and display.
  - Controller events are now recorded when playback is
    stopped. Time is not incremented. (It can be changed in
    the Event editor, if needed.)
  - Added an "Insert macro at L" function in the Tools popup menu.
  - Upgraded the MIDI control macro feature to allow multiple
    events in each macro, separated by " | ".
  - Changed event sorting to use a stable sort, modified event
    ranking to make CCs and Program Changes have the same priority,
    as part of fixes for issue #138.
  - Modified adding painted notes to the closest tick snap,
    also fixes adding notes while zoomed.
  - LFO.
    - Added a "DC Only" option.
    - Upgraded the LFO editor as per issue #139.
    - When using LFO, saving, then exiting via the main window
      a prompt about a needless save was removed.
    - Fixed the LFO for operation on pitchbend.
  - The drawing of scales was done incorrectly. Fixed both the
    seqroll grid drawing and the scales policy function.
  - Fixed the seqroll 'r' command (velocity randomization) to set
      the modify flag only if events are actually randomized.
  -   Fixed the drawing of "ghost notes" when moving or pasting
      notes.
  -   PPQN updates.
      -   Fixed the adding of painted notes (mostly) at PPQN other
          than the long-standing base default, 192.
      -   Changed the lowest PPQN from 32 to 24, for those who
          experiment. Also added PPQN = 48.
      -   Fixed File / New to reset PPQN to the default (192)
          and the tempo to the value set in the 'usr' file.
      -   Fixed the handling of MIDI file PPQN to set initial
          zoom correctly for all supported PPQNs, and when "0"
          is clicked, in the pattern and song editors.
  -   Updated the time-signature handling as per issue #137.
- Song editor.
  - Fixed the editbase snap_x function.
  - Optimized gradient drawing using QLinearGradient members in
    qperfroll and qperfnames instead of auto objects.
- Event editor.
- Preferences dialog.
  - Fixed the enabling/disabling of entries in the control and
    display combo-boxes based on status of control and display.
  - Provide a warning when using ALSA "Midi Through" ports for
    both control and display, which can lead to weird stuff.
  - Detection of this at startup has been added. An error message
    is posted and MIDI Control and Display disabled, for safety.
- Contrib files.
- Configuration files.
  - Macros in libseq66/include/seq66_features.h:
    - SEQ66_USE_COLLAPSED_SLOT_POPUP_MENU
    - SEQ66_DRAW_PITCHBEND_AS_DOT (undefined)
- Documentation. Updated with fixes and new features.
- Classes.
  - midifile class.
    - SeqSpecs with no data were read improperly.
    - Cleaned up the handling of time signatures and the c_timesig
      SeqSpec. The earliest time-signature event, if present,
      overrides the c_timesig SeqSpec.
    - Added a time signature event at the beginning of a track.
    - SMF 0 Import. Meta events are now stored in pattern 0.
      Load contrib/midi/CountryStrum.mid for an example.
  - performer. Changed default 32nds-per-quarter-note from 0 to 8.
  - sequence. Used new MIDI default values and fixed an
    index error in add_timesig_event(). 

See NEWS for more details.

